    "Therefore, the input data x t at time t consist of all eight factors, x t = {P t, T t, LW t, SW t, RH t, WS t, ST t, SM t-1 }.",
    "As groundwater level observations are difficult to obtain, changes in the lower boundary conditions are excluded from the inputs.",
    "Figure 3 shows the autocorrelation analysis conducted at five soil depths.",
    "The autocorrelation coefficients for soil water content at different depths decrease with an increasing number of delay days.",
    "The most significant change is observed in the surface layer."
